eaningful comparison of the two systems.</div><div>9. Collecting <em>data</em> is a painfully slow process.</div><div>10. Roberts has spent much of his working life collating the <em>data</em> on which the study was based.</div><div>11. You need a long series of <em>data</em> to be able to discern such a trend.</div><div>12. The <em>data</em> are then fed into a computer.</div><div>13. These <em>data</em> show that most cancers are detected as a result of clinical follow - up .</div><div>14. This theory needs to be backed up with solid empirical <em>data</em>/evidence.</div><div>15. Further analysis of the <em>data</em> is needed.</div><div>16. Statistical anomalies can make it difficult to compare economic <em>data</em> from one year to the next.</div><div>17. They have proprietary rights to the <em>data</em>.</div><div>18. Other recommendations relate to the details of how such <em>data</em> is stored.</div><div>19. The <em>data</em> is stored on the magnetic tape.</div><div>20. "<em>Data</em>" is the Latin plural form of "datum".</div><div>21. The <em>data</em> you have collected is not enough to be convincing.</div><div>22. The research involves collecting <em>data</em> from two random samples.</div><div>23. The company's role is to repurpose print <em>data</em> for use on the Web.</div><div>24. If the input <em>data</em> specified it, the file will close and the process terminates.</div><div>25. The <em>data</em> is stored on a hard disk and backed up on a floppy disk.</div><div>26. It would be dishonest not to present the <em>data</em> as fairly as possible.</div><div>27. Experienced users have direct access to the main <em>data</em> files.</div><div>28. No conversion from analogue to digital <em>data</em> is needed.</div><div>29. Given <em>data</em> which are free from bias there are further snares to avoid in statistical work.</div><div style="margin-bottom:3px;">30. The sheer amount of <em>data</em> makes the mind boggle.</div></div><!--student结束-->    <div id="ad_marginbottom_0" style="padding-top:0px;margin-bottom:6px;line-height:normal;margin-top:-8px;">  <script async src="//pagead2.googlesyndication.com/pagead/js/adsbygoogle.js"></script>  <!-- 728_90_20170421 -->  <ins class="adsbygoogle"       style="display:inline-block;width:728px;height:90px"       data-ad-client="ca-pub-7200850114163593"       data-ad-slot="2392632666"></ins>  <script>  (adsbygoogle = window.adsbygoogle || []).push({});  </script>  </div>  <div style="margin-bottom:3px;font-size:13px;line-height:21px;"><span style="font-weight:bold;float:left;display:block">More similar words:&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='database.html' target='_blank'>database</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='at all.html' target='_blank'>at all</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='fatal.html' target='_blank'>fatal</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='not at all.html' target='_blank'>not at all</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='candidate.html' target='_blank'>candidate</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='update.html' target='_blank'>update</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='to date.html' target='_blank'>to date</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='mandate.html' target='_blank'>mandate</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='catalog.html' target='_blank'>catalog</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='at a loss.html' target='_blank'>at a loss</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='at a time.html' target='_blank'>at a time</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='at any rate.html' target='_blank'>at any rate</a>,&nbsp;</span><span style='float:left;display:block;'><a href='be good at.html' target='_blank'>be good at</a>,&nbsp;</span>